If $x + \frac{1}{x} = 5,$ then compute the value of
\[(x - 2)^2 + \frac{25}{(x - 2)^2}.\]

Solution:
We can write
\begin{align*}
(x - 2)^2 + \frac{25}{(x - 2)^2} &= (x - 2)^2 + \frac{5^2}{(x - 2)^2} \\
&= (x - 2)^2 + 2 \cdot (x - 2) \cdot \frac{5}{x - 2} + \frac{5^2}{(x - 2)^2} - 2 \cdot (x - 2) \cdot \frac{5}{x - 2} \\
&= \left( (x - 2) + \frac{5}{x - 2} \right)^2 - 10 \\
&= \left( x - 2 + \frac{5}{x - 2} \right)^2 - 10 \\
&= \left( x + \frac{1}{x - 2} \right)^2 - 10.
\end{align*}From $x + \frac{1}{x} = 5,$ $x^2 + 1 = 5x,$ so $x^2 - 5x + 1 = 0.$  Then
\[x^2 - 5x + 1 = (x - 2)^2 - 5(x - 2) + 1 = 0.\]Hence, $x - 2 + \frac{1}{x - 2} = 5,$ so
\[\left( x + \frac{1}{x - 2} \right)^2 - 10 = 5^2 - 10 = \boxed{15}.\]
